meta.name: COVID-19 Simulator - Simulator
meta.description: An interactive tool developed by researchers at Mass General Hospital, Harvard Medical School, Georgia Tech and Boston Medical Center to inform COVID-19 intervention policy decisions in the US. Click for more.

meta.name: CovidAnalytics at MIT - DELPHI
meta.description: This model predicts based on an SEIR model augmented with underdetection and interventions. Projections account for reopening and assume interventions would be re-enacted if cases continue to climb. Click for more.

meta.name: GT - DeepCOVID
meta.description: Data-driven approach based on deep learning for forecasting mortality and hospitalizations using syndromic, clinical, demographic, mobility and point-of-care data. Click for more.

meta.name: Georgia Institute of Technology Center for Health and Humanitarian Systems - COVID19
meta.description: Agent-based simulation model to project COVID19 infection spread. Click for more.

meta.name: University of Geneva / Swiss Data Science Center - DeterministicGrowth
meta.description: We calculate the growth rate of cumulative cases (resp. deaths) between two days ago and today. If greater than 5%, we use an exponential model to forecast. Otherwise, we use a linear model. Click for more.

meta.name: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation - CurveFit
meta.description: This model makes predictions about the future that are dependent on the assumption that current interventions continue. Non-linear mixed efects curve-fitting. Click for more.

meta.name: Imperial - Ensemble2
meta.description: A disease transmission model with no assumptions about the future intervention strategies. Click for more.

meta.name: Iowa State - Lily Wang's Research Group - Spatiotemporal Epidemic Modeling
meta.description: Spatiotemporal Dynamics, Nowcasting and Forecasting of COVID-19 in the United States. Click for more.

meta.name: Johns Hopkins ID Dynamics COVID-19 Working Group - CovidScenarioPipeline
meta.description: County-level metapopulation model with commuting and stochastic SEIR disease dynamics with social-distancing indicators. Click for more.

meta.name: Los Alamos National Labs - GrowthRate
meta.description: This model makes predictions about the future, unconditional on particular intervention strategies. Statistical dynamical growth model accounting for population susceptibility. Click for more.

meta.name: COVID Alliance at MIT - Two-Stage SIR
meta.description: SIR model trained on public heath regions. SIR parameters are functions of static demographic and time-varying mobility features. Two-stage approach that first learns magnitude of peak infections. Click for more.

meta.name: MOBS Lab at Northeastern - GLEAM COVID-19
meta.description: This model makes predictions about the future that are dependent on the assumption that current interventions continue. Metapopulation, age structured SLIR model. Click for more.

meta.name: NotreDame-FRED - NotreDame-FRED
meta.description: FRED is an agent-based model developed for influenza with parameters modified to represent the natural history of COVID-19 Click for more.

meta.name: NotreDame-mobility - NotreDame-mobility
meta.description: This is an ensemble of nine models that are identical except that they are driven by different mobility indices from Apple and Google. The model underlying each is a deterministic, SEIR-like model. Click for more.

meta.name: Oliver Wyman - Pandemic Navigator
meta.description: Oliver Wyman's Pandemic Navigator provides forecasts & scenario analysis for Detected and Undetected cases and death counts following a compartmental formulation with non-stationary transition rates. Click for more.

meta.name: Predictive Science Inc - Disease Rapid Analysis and Forecasting Tool
meta.description: A stochastic/deterministic, single-population SEIRX model that stratifies by both age distribution and disease severity and includes generic intervention fitting. Click for more.

meta.name: QJHong - Encounter
meta.description: today's "Daily New Confirmed Cases" + today's "Encounter Density" ==> today's newly infected Cases ==> next 2-3 weeks' "Daily New Confirmed Cases" Click for more.

meta.name: Quantori modeling - The Agent-based local stochastic model of COVID-19
meta.description: The Agent-based local stochastic model of COVID-19 transmission Click for more.

meta.name: STH - 3 Phase Unadjusted
meta.description: Model assumes pandemics hit in 3 distinct phases. Each phase can be represented by a single variable and therefore the variables can be isolated. Click for more.

meta.name: Snyder Wilson Consulting - Terminus Compartmental Model
meta.description: Terminus is a mechanistic Compartmental Model using disease parameter estimates from literature. It uses Bayesian inference to predict the most likely model parameters. Click for more.

meta.name: University of Arizona - EpiGro Covid-19 model with Data Assimilation
meta.description: SIR mechanistic model with data assimilation. Click for more.

meta.name: UCLA Statistical Machine Learning Lab - SuEIR
meta.description: The SuEIR model is a variant of the SEIR model considering both untested and unreported cases. The model considers reopening and assumes susceptible population will increase after the reopen. Click for more.

meta.name: University of Chicago - CovidIL
meta.description: This is a compartmental, age-structured SEIR model that infers past SARS-CoV-2 transmission rates and forecasts mortality under current and hypothetical public health interventions. Click for more.

meta.name: University of Chicago - CovidIL_10_increase
meta.description: This is a compartmental, age-structured SEIR model that infers past SARS-CoV-2 transmission rates and forecasts mortality under current and hypothetical public health interventions. Click for more.

meta.name: University of Chicago - CovidIL_30_increase
meta.description: This is a compartmental, age-structured SEIR model that infers past SARS-CoV-2 transmission rates and forecasts mortality under current and hypothetical public health interventions. Click for more.

meta.name: University of Michigan COVID-19 Forecasting Group - RidgeTensorFlowRegressor
meta.description: Nation-level model of confirmed cases and deaths based on ridge regression. No assumptions made about social distancing. Click for more.

meta.name: UMass-Amherst Influenza Forecasting Center of Excellence & College of Information and Computer Sciences - MechBayes
meta.description: Bayesian compartmental model with observations on cumulative case counts and cumulative deaths. Model is fit independently to each state. Model includes observation noise and a case detection rate. Click for more.

meta.name: US Army Engineer Research and Development Center - ERDC_SEIR
meta.description: The ERDC SEIR model makes predictions of several variables (e.g., reported new/cumulative cases per day, etc.). Model parameters are estimated using historical data using Bayesian inference. Click for more.

meta.name: University of Southern California Data Science Lab - SI_kJalpha
meta.description: A heterogeneous infection rate model with human mobility for epidemic modeling. Our model adapts to changing trends and provide predictions of confirmed cases and deaths. Click for more.

meta.name: UT-Austin COVID-19 Consortium - Mobility
meta.description: This model makes predictions assuming that social distancing patterns, as measured by anonymized mobile-phone GPS traces, remain constant in the future.This model models only *first-wave deaths*. Click for more.

meta.name: YYG - ParamSearch
meta.description: Based on the SEIR model to make daily projections regarding COVID-19 infections and deaths in 50 US states. The model accounts for state reopenings and its effects on infections and deaths. Click for more.

meta.name: EpiForecasts group at the London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine - ensemble1
meta.description: A deaths forecast using the renewal equation and time-series forecasts of the time-varying reproduction number. Click for more.
